00:03:10.940 --> 00:03:14.777
DRAGAN MILEVIC
war criminal

38
00:03:22.618 --> 00:03:24.661
(French): Code 3.
Priest's in the church.

39
00:04:11.625 --> 00:04:13.960
(indistinct shouting)
(man grunting)

40
00:04:20.259 --> 00:04:21.718
- Ooh!
(men shouting)

41
00:04:21.844 --> 00:04:24.763
- Don't move!
(indistinct shouting)

42
00:04:24.889 --> 00:04:26.599
Go!

43
00:04:26.724 --> 00:04:29.309
Go! Go! Don't move!
You don't move!

44
00:04:29.435 --> 00:04:32.062
Don't move! Look at me.
(shouting)

45
00:04:32.188 --> 00:04:34.440
(screaming)

46
00:04:48.829 --> 00:04:49.913
- Clear.

47
00:05:18.317 --> 00:05:21.194
- Fuckin'... Sonofabitch.

48
00:05:30.830 --> 00:05:33.833
(grunting)
- Oops. I'm so sorry.

49
00:06:18.002 --> 00:06:21.213
AFGHANISTAN
Kabul

50
00:06:29.972 --> 00:06:31.682
- Is it recording?

51
00:06:31.807 --> 00:06:33.433
- Uh... Yes.

52
00:06:35.269 --> 00:06:37.354
What are you doing?

53
00:06:37.479 --> 00:06:38.813
- There's nothing left to hide.

54
00:06:41.692 --> 00:06:43.568
Do you remember
your first visit to Kabul?

55
00:06:43.694 --> 00:06:46.905
- Of course.
(buzzing)

56
00:06:47.698 --> 00:06:50.826
I'm sorry.
- I told you the story

57
00:06:50.951 --> 00:06:53.370
about that little girl
that was sold to settle a debit.

58
00:06:53.495 --> 00:06:54.454
- Mm-hmm.

59
00:06:54.580 --> 00:06:55.581
- And you said.

60
00:06:55.706 --> 00:06:58.542
"The only way
to change the world--"

61
00:06:58.667 --> 00:07:02.420
- Is to change the story.
Yes. I remember.

62
00:07:07.009 --> 00:07:08.260
- So now...

63
00:07:09.261 --> 00:07:10.637
I want to tell you mine.

64
00:07:12.514 --> 00:07:15.600
My mother was in love
with one man.

65
00:07:15.726 --> 00:07:19.020
but her family forced her
to marry another.

66
00:07:19.146 --> 00:07:21.064
As her children.
we watched her every day

67
00:07:21.190 --> 00:07:23.525
as she tried to erase

68
00:07:23.651 --> 00:07:25.611
her shame of infidelity.

69
00:07:25.736 --> 00:07:27.654
Until one day...

70
00:07:29.448 --> 00:07:31.908
...She went out into the garden

71
00:07:32.034 --> 00:07:33.869
and poured petrol on her face.

72
00:07:35.454 --> 00:07:37.539
And she lit a match.

73
00:07:39.083 --> 00:07:41.752
Our older sister. Aisha.
that same night.

74
00:07:41.877 --> 00:07:43.086
her husband put a knife

75
00:07:43.212 --> 00:07:47.299
to her face. to punish her
for having such a weak mother.

76
00:07:50.761 --> 00:07:52.679
- So the little girl
that was sold was you?

77
00:07:55.057 --> 00:07:58.852
Why you telling me this now?
- To protect you from Zaief.

78
00:07:58.978 --> 00:08:00.771
- What's the connection to Zaief?

79
00:08:00.896 --> 00:08:03.481
- How do you think
I know so much about him?

80
00:08:03.607 --> 00:08:06.276
It's to Zaief's family that I was sold.

81
00:08:08.696 --> 00:08:11.699
- Why are you risking showing
your face to the camera. then?

82
00:08:11.824 --> 00:08:13.700
- Because this is the last time
we see each other.

83
00:08:13.826 --> 00:08:16.453
- What do you mean?
- Elsa. Zaief knows.

84
00:08:16.578 --> 00:08:18.204
He found out.

85
00:08:18.330 --> 00:08:22.125
I'm sorry. I must go now.
- Maina. please wait!

86
00:08:22.251 --> 00:08:24.461
Please stay. I can get you out.
Please. come with me.

87
00:08:24.586 --> 00:08:26.629
- You must go and change my story.

88
00:08:26.755 --> 00:08:29.215
Go back and never return.

89
00:08:30.134 --> 00:08:32.886
- Amin. not now! Maina!
- The house has been spotted.

90
00:08:33.012 --> 00:08:34.638
- Maina!
- You have to get out of there.

91
00:08:34.763 --> 00:08:36.556
You and Maina have to leave right now.

92
00:08:36.682 --> 00:08:38.225
- Who are "they"?
- You hear me?

93
00:08:38.350 --> 00:08:39.351
- Ah. merde!

94
00:08:39.476 --> 00:08:41.728
- Elsa. leave now!
- Yes.

95
00:08:41.854 --> 00:08:43.730
Yes. pull up the car.

96
00:08:45.733 --> 00:08:46.942
She split.

97
00:08:51.155 --> 00:08:53.073
We gotta go find her.

98
00:08:53.198 --> 00:08:55.325
- It is out of the question.
- Listen. she's in danger.

99
00:08:55.451 --> 00:08:57.161
We have to go by her house.

100
00:08:57.953 --> 00:09:00.038
- You'll be even more in danger
if you go there.

101
00:09:00.164 --> 00:09:01.373
- Amin. just do it!

102
00:09:03.042 --> 00:09:04.084
Take a right here.

103
00:09:04.752 --> 00:09:06.170
(honking)

104
00:09:07.796 --> 00:09:09.130
(indistinct shouting)

105
00:09:18.474 --> 00:09:19.808
- Get down. get down!
Hide. hide!

106
00:09:24.980 --> 00:09:26.606
(shouting)

107
00:09:33.155 --> 00:09:36.408
FRANCE
Special Forces base

108
00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:41.621
(French): I couldn't have said yes.

109
00:09:42.164 --> 00:09:43.498
I was meeting mom.

110
00:09:44.374 --> 00:09:45.583
- Your mom hates me.

111
00:09:45.876 --> 00:09:47.460
Don't slam the door. please.

112
00:09:47.628 --> 00:09:49.671
- Hate? No.
She thinks you're immature.

113
00:09:49.838 --> 00:09:51.256
- I'm not immature.

114
00:09:51.423 --> 00:09:52.215
- You're not?

115
00:09:52.382 --> 00:09:53.716
- Go easy on the door.

116
00:09:53.884 --> 00:09:56.344
- It's a heap of stinking metal!

117
00:09:57.554 --> 00:10:00.682
(rock music)
Drunken eyes heavy sighs

118
00:10:00.808 --> 00:10:03.310
Watching the floor
Count the days cried

119
00:10:03.435 --> 00:10:05.937
The past has died you are free

120
00:10:06.063 --> 00:10:08.273
(indistinct chatter)

121
00:10:08.398 --> 00:10:09.816
- He doesn't know?
- No.

122
00:10:12.653 --> 00:10:13.820
-Am I immature?

123
00:10:14.404 --> 00:10:15.196
- Immature?

124
00:10:17.741 --> 00:10:18.783
- Cut it out.

125
00:10:20.160 --> 00:10:21.578
- What's the problem?

126
00:10:21.995 --> 00:10:23.913
- Lisa wants us to live together.

127
00:10:24.081 --> 00:10:24.664
- What?

128
00:10:25.332 --> 00:10:27.667
After only 6 years together?

129
00:10:30.295 --> 00:10:31.212
- I know.

130
00:10:31.380 --> 00:10:32.714
The time's flown by.

131
00:10:33.757 --> 00:10:35.341
I'll have to sell the car.

132
00:10:35.717 --> 00:10:38.386
Then we'll get a Labrador.

133
00:10:38.804 --> 00:10:40.722
Then decorate a bedroom.

134
00:10:42.933 --> 00:10:44.893
- Happy birthday!
- Thanks.

135
00:10:47.020 --> 00:10:49.355
KABUL
Hotel Merindi

136
00:10:49.481 --> 00:10:50.773
- What do you wanna do?

137
00:10:53.485 --> 00:10:56.154
Elsa. Maybe it's time
to take that holiday

138
00:10:56.280 --> 00:10:59.491
you've been talking about.
- Pick me up in two hours.

139
00:11:11.879 --> 00:11:13.422
- You're a pain in the butt.

140
00:11:14.965 --> 00:11:18.510
- This compass saved a unit's lives
in the Normandy Landings.

141
00:11:19.094 --> 00:11:20.678
It's a museum piece.

142
00:11:21.054 --> 00:11:23.056
We all chipped in to buy it.

143
00:11:23.557 --> 00:11:24.933
Happy birthday. brother.

144
00:11:25.100 --> 00:11:27.185
(all wishing him happy birthday)
- Wow!

145
00:11:28.312 --> 00:11:30.439
- Ah!

146
00:11:35.944 --> 00:11:37.904
(honking)

147
00:11:45.329 --> 00:11:48.206
- I hope Salemani can help us find her.

148
00:11:48.332 --> 00:11:51.084
- Maina's gone. There's nothing
you can do for her anymore.

149
00:11:52.628 --> 00:11:54.630
- I can't just abandon her!

150
00:12:15.359 --> 00:12:17.444
(clanging)

151
00:12:19.905 --> 00:12:21.114
- Salemani?

152
00:12:24.660 --> 00:12:26.370
(clanging)

153
00:12:26.954 --> 00:12:28.956
- Salemani?
- Here!

154
00:12:32.376 --> 00:12:33.960
Asalaam aleikum.

155
00:12:34.086 --> 00:12:35.754
- Aleikum salaam.

156
00:12:37.172 --> 00:12:38.882
Please. Salemani.

157
00:12:39.800 --> 00:12:41.176
I need your help.

158
00:12:42.552 --> 00:12:44.595
I want to talk to Zaief.

159
00:12:46.181 --> 00:12:48.141
I need to find Maina.

160
00:12:49.393 --> 00:12:51.478
- I don't know any Zaief.

161
00:12:51.603 --> 00:12:53.187
(distant clanging)

162
00:12:54.189 --> 00:12:57.442
I'm so sorry. Elsa.
I had no choice.

163
00:13:00.988 --> 00:13:03.949
(dramatic music)
(panting)

164
00:13:04.074 --> 00:13:05.867
(screaming)
- Shhh-shhh-shhh...

165
00:13:05.993 --> 00:13:08.120
Keep it down! Come on.

166
00:13:08.245 --> 00:13:09.788
(engine revving)

167
00:13:14.459 --> 00:13:16.419
You okay?
- Yes.

168
00:13:26.638 --> 00:13:27.805
(speaking Urdu)

169
00:13:28.557 --> 00:13:29.224
- Back up!

170
00:13:38.275 --> 00:13:39.651
- This isn't happening!

171
00:13:41.403 --> 00:13:42.654
- Hide your face.

172
00:13:45.699 --> 00:13:48.118
(shouting)

173
00:13:48.243 --> 00:13:49.953
(speaking Urdu)

174
00:13:54.416 --> 00:13:57.252
(automatic gunfire)

175
00:13:59.171 --> 00:14:02.299
(Elsa screaming)
(grunting)

176
00:14:02.424 --> 00:14:03.550
(screaming)

177
00:14:04.092 --> 00:14:05.009
- Seen Jacques?

178
00:14:05.177 --> 00:14:06.344
- Right there.

179
00:14:06.803 --> 00:14:08.846
PARIS
Elsa Casanova's newsroom

180
00:14:09.556 --> 00:14:11.307
- Foreign Minister for you.

181
00:14:11.975 --> 00:14:13.685
- Yes. Jacques Beauregard.

182
00:14:13.852 --> 00:14:15.562
Good morning. Minister.

183
00:14:17.397 --> 00:14:18.356
Sorry?

184
00:14:19.066 --> 00:14:20.067
What?

185
00:14:21.735 --> 00:14:23.069
- What's going on?
- No idea.

186
00:14:23.362 --> 00:14:24.196
(phone vibrating)

187
00:14:25.447 --> 00:14:26.448
- Yes?

188
00:14:28.033 --> 00:14:29.034
- Yes. admiral.

189
00:14:30.535 --> 00:14:31.661
Very well.

190
00:14:35.290 --> 00:14:37.500
- Elsa's been abducted by the Taliban.

191
00:14:47.094 --> 00:14:48.845
PARIS
Elysée Palace

192
00:14:56.770 --> 00:14:58.480
NATIONAL SECURITY COUNCIL
Green room

193
00:14:59.606 --> 00:15:02.233
- Can our intelligence expert
tell us more?

194
00:15:02.692 --> 00:15:04.402
- Zaief is a fanatic.

195
00:15:04.569 --> 00:15:05.945
Totally unpredictable.

196
00:15:06.279 --> 00:15:07.905
- I want her back alive.

197
00:15:08.949 --> 00:15:09.950
Is that clear?

198
00:15:10.117 --> 00:15:12.911
- Do we have any idea where they are?

199
00:15:13.078 --> 00:15:15.121
- In his tribal stronghold.

200
00:15:15.539 --> 00:15:17.666
Zaief thinks he's untouchable.

201
00:15:18.375 --> 00:15:21.461
- We can send in
a special forces unit.

202
00:15:21.628 --> 00:15:22.503
- How many men?

203
00:15:22.671 --> 00:15:23.505
- Around sixty.

204
00:15:23.672 --> 00:15:24.297
- How soon?

205
00:15:24.631 --> 00:15:27.133
- Some have already taken off.
Mr. President.

206
00:15:35.600 --> 00:15:39.020
AFGHANISTAN
Wardak Province

207
00:15:48.071 --> 00:15:49.572
(Middle Eastern music)

208
00:16:12.554 --> 00:16:13.471
- Your chopper.

209
00:16:13.638 --> 00:16:15.097
We'll send your gear on.

210
00:16:59.434 --> 00:17:02.687
AFGHAN-PAKISTAN BORDER
Gandamak Camp

211
00:17:26.086 --> 00:17:28.088
- See the fat guy over there?

212
00:17:28.255 --> 00:17:29.798
Let's play a joke on him.

213
00:17:33.468 --> 00:17:34.760
(gunfire)

214
00:17:40.892 --> 00:17:42.810
- My method is simple.

215
00:17:43.979 --> 00:17:45.313
One line on the left.

216
00:17:45.480 --> 00:17:46.898
one line on the right.

217
00:17:47.065 --> 00:17:49.275
If you step out of line.

218
00:17:49.442 --> 00:17:51.694
I set you straight. My way.

219
00:17:54.823 --> 00:17:58.952
You're all gonna learn
to spit thunder out front

220
00:17:59.119 --> 00:18:00.995
and fart lightning out behind.

221
00:18:09.713 --> 00:18:11.297
(groaning)

222
00:18:12.799 --> 00:18:14.467
- Back in this shithole.

223
00:18:17.387 --> 00:18:19.013
- Air Force boy on beach vacation?

224
00:18:19.639 --> 00:18:20.598
- He's with us.

225
00:18:21.099 --> 00:18:22.058
- What?

226
00:18:32.777 --> 00:18:35.237
- Victor. put your pop gun away.

227
00:18:35.614 --> 00:18:37.449
The boss is here. He's waiting.

228
00:18:38.241 --> 00:18:40.284
- What's with the t-shirt?

229
00:18:40.452 --> 00:18:42.328
- I got you one. Kiddie size.

230
00:18:43.538 --> 00:18:44.539
- Ow!

231
00:18:44.664 --> 00:18:45.831
- My canary!

232
00:18:45.999 --> 00:18:47.625
You're my little canary!

233
00:18:47.751 --> 00:18:49.127
(laughter)

234
00:18:57.344 --> 00:18:58.970
(panting)

235
00:19:11.149 --> 00:19:12.984
- You all right?

236
00:19:37.592 --> 00:19:39.385
(exhaling forcefully)

237
00:19:44.015 --> 00:19:46.183
- I'm so sorry. Amin.

238
00:19:47.185 --> 00:19:49.187
I should've listened to you.

239
00:19:54.192 --> 00:19:56.027
- Don't be sorry.

240
00:19:59.406 --> 00:20:01.199
(Elsa sniffling)

241
00:20:11.626 --> 00:20:13.210
- I'm scared.

242
00:20:16.047 --> 00:20:18.299
- Don't surrender to fear...

243
00:20:18.425 --> 00:20:20.051
You hear me?

244
00:20:21.219 --> 00:20:23.429
Don't show them your fear.

245
00:20:26.057 --> 00:20:28.100
They can kill us.
but they never can defeat us.

246
00:20:28.226 --> 00:20:30.061
You understand?

247
00:20:33.732 --> 00:20:35.150
(French): Commander! Captain!

248
00:20:35.525 --> 00:20:36.317
- Commander!

249
00:20:36.484 --> 00:20:37.109
- Gentlemen.

250
00:20:38.611 --> 00:20:40.070
(sniffing)

251
00:20:41.072 --> 00:20:42.615
Yes. we have a new sniper.

252
00:20:42.782 --> 00:20:44.366
- New and never been fucked.

253
00:20:44.534 --> 00:20:45.493
- Distance record?

254
00:20:45.660 --> 00:20:47.703
- I killed a rabbit at 253 meters.

255
00:20:47.996 --> 00:20:48.746
- Okay!

256
00:20:49.748 --> 00:20:50.665
- Murderer!

257
00:20:50.832 --> 00:20:51.707
- As usual.

258
00:20:52.041 --> 00:20:54.001
there's good and bad news.

259
00:20:54.169 --> 00:20:55.628
- Rabbit's on the menu.

260
00:20:56.629 --> 00:20:57.463
- The bad news...

261
00:20:58.840 --> 00:21:00.591
The hostages are in Pakistan.

262
00:21:00.759 --> 00:21:01.926
In the tribal areas.

263
00:21:02.093 --> 00:21:03.094
- Happy birthday!

264
00:21:03.636 --> 00:21:06.221
- The good news is
it's only reconnaissance.

265
00:21:06.389 --> 00:21:09.141
- For once. we're in the front row.
not on stage.

266
00:21:09.726 --> 00:21:10.727
- Questions?

267
00:21:10.894 --> 00:21:12.061
- For your information.

268
00:21:12.228 --> 00:21:14.647
Casanova opposes our presence here.

269
00:21:14.814 --> 00:21:16.106
- Any other questions?

270
00:21:16.274 --> 00:21:17.441
- Yeah.

271
00:21:18.234 --> 00:21:19.276
Is she pretty?

272
00:21:19.486 --> 00:21:21.529
(laughter)

273
00:21:25.325 --> 00:21:27.618
(man speaking Urdu)

274
00:21:27.744 --> 00:21:28.995
(Elsa crying out)
- Please!

275
00:21:29.120 --> 00:21:30.788
(gun clicking)
(Elsa crying out)

276
00:21:30.914 --> 00:21:32.332
(men laughing)

277
00:21:34.501 --> 00:21:35.710
(panting)

278
00:21:35.835 --> 00:21:37.837
- Shhh.
(dog yapping)

279
00:21:38.922 --> 00:21:40.298
Shhh.

280
00:21:43.343 --> 00:21:47.096
- Why didn't you ask me
for an interview?

281
00:21:47.222 --> 00:21:50.141
That would've been the civilized way
to go about things.

282
00:21:50.934 --> 00:21:52.727
- Civilized?

283
00:21:55.313 --> 00:21:57.523
- You call me
"the Butcher of Kabul."

284
00:21:58.733 --> 00:22:00.317
"Afghan Women's Worst Friend."

285
00:22:01.402 --> 00:22:04.154
Wasn't that the title
of your last article?

286
00:22:06.533 --> 00:22:08.826
- What have you done to Maina?

287
00:22:09.744 --> 00:22:11.537
- What have I done to Maina?

288
00:22:14.958 --> 00:22:17.001
What have your lies done to Maina?

289
00:22:19.921 --> 00:22:21.547
Oh. I know you.

290
00:22:23.174 --> 00:22:24.800
Your family - so great.

291
00:22:25.760 --> 00:22:28.179
Your studies.
And look at you now.

292
00:22:28.304 --> 00:22:31.974
Sitting here like a... dog.

293
00:22:35.979 --> 00:22:38.564
- Seven brilliant years at Cambridge.

294
00:22:40.775 --> 00:22:42.568
Son of Munia Zaief Khan.

295
00:22:43.778 --> 00:22:46.197
The most powerful and influential chief.

296
00:22:52.579 --> 00:22:55.582
And yet... you're sitting here with me.

297
00:22:59.836 --> 00:23:02.213
Only you chose to be here.

298
00:23:06.384 --> 00:23:07.802
- Did I invite you...

299
00:23:07.927 --> 00:23:09.803
into my country?

300
00:23:11.222 --> 00:23:14.934
Spread democracy at gunpoint
and drive my people crazy?

301
00:23:16.019 --> 00:23:19.188
- It's still better than selling
a 12-year-old child.

302
00:23:27.238 --> 00:23:28.989
- I believe in an interview.
it is customary

303
00:23:29.115 --> 00:23:31.617
for the person behind the camera
to be asking the questions.

304
00:23:36.247 --> 00:23:38.624
And I find this question
very appropriate right now.

305
00:23:40.251 --> 00:23:41.794
Do you...

306
00:23:41.920 --> 00:23:43.838
believe in God?

307
00:23:45.048 --> 00:23:47.842
- Yeah... I believe in God.

308
00:23:58.102 --> 00:23:59.853
- Out loud.

309
00:24:01.439 --> 00:24:03.065
Out loud!

310
00:24:10.657 --> 00:24:12.659
- I can't read this.

311
00:24:17.288 --> 00:24:18.580
(crying out)

312
00:24:21.292 --> 00:24:22.584
Why aren't you watching?!

313
00:24:22.710 --> 00:24:24.878
(panting)
Look at me!

314
00:24:31.469 --> 00:24:32.887
(Urdu): Stop.
(crying out)

315
00:24:34.222 --> 00:24:36.307
(panting)

316
00:24:36.599 --> 00:24:37.975
Bring in Salemani.

317
00:24:41.646 --> 00:24:44.565
(Salemani groaning)

318
00:24:49.320 --> 00:24:50.696
- Don't do this.

319
00:24:50.822 --> 00:24:52.323
Don't do this.

320
00:24:57.787 --> 00:24:59.121
- To sweeten his death.

321
00:24:59.914 --> 00:25:01.582
- Don't do this! Don't do this!

322
00:25:01.708 --> 00:25:03.960
- Ah! Ah! Ah!

323
00:25:06.129 --> 00:25:07.255
- Please don't.

324
00:25:07.380 --> 00:25:09.799
Don't do this!
(Salemani groaning)

325
00:25:09.924 --> 00:25:12.217
Don't do it!

326
00:25:12.343 --> 00:25:15.304
(Salemani struggling
and groaning)

327
00:25:23.938 --> 00:25:26.732
(dramatic music)
(sighing)

328
00:25:32.947 --> 00:25:36.742
CHARLES DE GAULLE
Aircraft carrier

329
00:25:54.010 --> 00:25:57.013
ADMIRAL GUEZENNEC
Special Operations Command

330
00:26:00.600 --> 00:26:02.101
(French): Permission to board. captain?

331
00:26:02.268 --> 00:26:03.602
- Permission granted. admiral.

332
00:26:03.853 --> 00:26:05.771
- Weather reports every half-hour.

333
00:26:06.773 --> 00:26:09.192
When they take off.
I gotta talk to Kovax.

334
00:26:12.445 --> 00:26:14.238
12 HOURS LATER
(Elsa): Don't do this!

335
00:26:14.363 --> 00:26:15.739
(Salemani groaning)
Don't do this!

336
00:26:16.282 --> 00:26:17.449
- Enough. turn it off.

337
00:26:17.617 --> 00:26:18.701
- He's sick.

338
00:26:18.868 --> 00:26:21.996
- No French woman will be decapitated
for the world to see.

339
00:26:22.747 --> 00:26:24.999
How long
before your men can intervene?

340
00:26:25.166 --> 00:26:26.000
- 24 hours.

341
00:26:26.167 --> 00:26:27.835
- In that case. we've lost.

342
00:26:28.002 --> 00:26:28.919
- Perhaps not.

343
00:26:29.087 --> 00:26:31.214
We have an ace up our sleeves.

344
00:26:43.684 --> 00:26:45.936
- That's the situation.

345
00:26:49.107 --> 00:26:50.983
- Slight change of plans.

346
00:26:58.574 --> 00:26:59.992
- The chances of success?

347
00:27:00.159 --> 00:27:02.995
- There are no guarantees
with these operations.

348
00:27:03.162 --> 00:27:04.788
That's why they're special.

349
00:27:08.000 --> 00:27:09.626
- Permission to proceed.

350
00:27:22.348 --> 00:27:23.515
- Double ammo time.

351
00:27:24.267 --> 00:27:26.143
- I love the job.

352
00:27:26.269 --> 00:27:27.144
- What's that?

353
00:27:27.395 --> 00:27:28.938
- I love the job.

354
00:27:29.063 --> 00:27:30.105
(laughter)

355
00:27:31.983 --> 00:27:33.526
- It's worth a shot.

356
00:27:33.651 --> 00:27:35.944
(laughter)

357
00:27:43.911 --> 00:27:45.662
(man): Open payload!

358
00:27:46.330 --> 00:27:50.167
DAY 1

359
00:27:50.376 --> 00:27:52.127
(heavy rock music)

360
00:27:55.173 --> 00:27:55.965
(man): In position.

361
00:28:01.429 --> 00:28:02.805
(man): 30 seconds.
(man 2): 30 seconds.

362
00:28:14.775 --> 00:28:15.567
10 seconds.

363
00:28:18.279 --> 00:28:18.904
3...

364
00:28:19.071 --> 00:28:19.821
2...

365
00:28:19.989 --> 00:28:20.489
1...

366
00:28:20.823 --> 00:28:21.907
Green!

367
00:29:05.952 --> 00:29:08.329
(wind blowing)

368
00:29:09.121 --> 00:29:12.624
PAKISTAN
Tribal Areas

369
00:29:20.758 --> 00:29:22.342
- Welcome to Pakistan. guys.

370
00:29:24.178 --> 00:29:26.471
(Middle Eastern music)

371
00:30:06.137 --> 00:30:07.972
- One hour to get in position.

372
00:30:08.848 --> 00:30:10.599
- No time to go shopping. then.

373
00:30:13.394 --> 00:30:15.437
(Middle Eastern music)

374
00:30:26.490 --> 00:30:28.658
PAKISTANI SECRET SERVICES

375
00:30:30.536 --> 00:30:32.955
MULLAH ZUKHAN
Taliban Spiritual Leader

376
00:31:06.113 --> 00:31:07.239
(door creaking open)

377
00:31:16.874 --> 00:31:18.500
- Asalaam aleikum.

378
00:31:19.001 --> 00:31:21.753
(Urdu): By Allah. the almighty Prophet.
welcome.

379
00:31:25.466 --> 00:31:27.384
Greetings. men of the Shura.

380
00:31:33.432 --> 00:31:34.599
- He didn't kill her.

381
00:31:34.767 --> 00:31:36.226
(man chuckling softly)

382
00:31:40.064 --> 00:31:41.982
- Many of our brothers think

383
00:31:42.274 --> 00:31:43.483
you can't be trusted.

384
00:31:44.735 --> 00:31:46.319
- On what grounds?

385
00:31:46.737 --> 00:31:48.864
- They say you work for your own glory

386
00:31:49.031 --> 00:31:51.199
rather than to achieve God's will.

387
00:31:53.369 --> 00:31:55.579
- I'm the Shura's loyal servant.

388
00:31:56.414 --> 00:31:58.624
- She's like those impure sluts

389
00:31:59.250 --> 00:32:01.627
he frequented in London.

390
00:32:04.380 --> 00:32:05.631
- Women are the weak point

391
00:32:06.257 --> 00:32:07.675
of the West.

392
00:32:09.760 --> 00:32:11.970
Don't be taken in again.

393
00:32:17.393 --> 00:32:18.977
If this woman is to die.

394
00:32:19.728 --> 00:32:22.105
it's a sign
she must go to meet Allah.

395
00:32:25.192 --> 00:32:27.277
Don't disappoint me.

396
00:32:55.306 --> 00:32:57.224
(French): Is it me
or are they multiplying?

397
00:32:57.600 --> 00:32:59.101
We need more men.

398
00:32:59.268 --> 00:33:01.603
- Shut it. Tic Tac.
Tell us where they are.

399
00:33:09.069 --> 00:33:11.362
- Satellite dishes
and barred windows...

400
00:33:11.697 --> 00:33:13.407
That's their holiday home.

401
00:33:15.034 --> 00:33:16.618
- Movement. 3 o'clock.

402
00:33:20.372 --> 00:33:21.581
- What are they doing?

403
00:33:23.501 --> 00:33:24.919
- Stay put.

404
00:33:26.212 --> 00:33:27.213
- We just watch?

405
00:33:28.255 --> 00:33:29.256
- Yes.

406
00:33:30.132 --> 00:33:31.133
- Why?

407
00:33:32.134 --> 00:33:33.677
- That's not why we're here.

408
00:33:37.765 --> 00:33:39.141
- Not why we're here.

409
00:33:47.566 --> 00:33:49.693
(gunfire)

410
00:34:06.168 --> 00:34:08.253
(speaking Urdu)

411
00:34:08.879 --> 00:34:10.505
- In English. please.

412
00:34:10.631 --> 00:34:13.258
I've had enough
of this language for one day.

413
00:34:16.470 --> 00:34:19.473
- What are you gonna do
with French journalist?

414
00:34:21.058 --> 00:34:23.060
(sighing)
- I don't know.

415
00:34:24.853 --> 00:34:26.688
I really don't know.

416
00:34:29.817 --> 00:34:30.526
- Showtime!

417
00:34:30.693 --> 00:34:32.695
(heavy rock music)

418
00:34:58.053 --> 00:34:59.304
(gunfire)

419
00:35:05.728 --> 00:35:07.479
(panting)

420
00:35:27.750 --> 00:35:28.959
- Okay.

421
00:35:29.168 --> 00:35:29.793
- Elias.

422
00:35:30.085 --> 00:35:31.086
you with us?

423
00:35:31.253 --> 00:35:31.962
- Right here.

424
00:35:33.005 --> 00:35:34.297
- On 3.

425
00:35:35.257 --> 00:35:36.174
1...

426
00:35:37.760 --> 00:35:38.761
2...

427
00:35:39.511 --> 00:35:39.928
31

428
00:35:48.020 --> 00:35:50.147
(heavy rock music)

429
00:36:14.004 --> 00:36:15.088
- Clear!

430
00:36:21.387 --> 00:36:22.763
- Ah!

431
00:36:24.640 --> 00:36:26.516
(gunfire)
- Ah!

432
00:36:33.065 --> 00:36:34.024
- Clear!

433
00:36:36.402 --> 00:36:37.027
- Clear!

434
00:36:39.196 --> 00:36:41.156
- Go. go. go. go. go. go. go. go. go!

435
00:36:45.035 --> 00:36:46.786
- Go. go. go. go. go!
- They're here!

436
00:36:46.995 --> 00:36:48.121
- We're getting you out!

437
00:36:49.456 --> 00:36:50.039
- Keep calm!

438
00:36:52.292 --> 00:36:52.917
- Hi!

439
00:36:53.585 --> 00:36:55.003
- Elsa Casanova?

440
00:36:56.046 --> 00:36:56.796
Amin Takharoud?

441
00:36:58.674 --> 00:36:59.549
Turn around!

442
00:37:05.764 --> 00:37:07.432
You're gonna follow
my instructions.

443
00:37:07.558 --> 00:37:08.809
Got that?
- Yes.

444
00:37:19.111 --> 00:37:20.654
- They know we're here.
- Out!

445
00:37:22.656 --> 00:37:23.615
Head down.

446
00:37:41.049 --> 00:37:42.383
(whispering)

447
00:37:58.984 --> 00:38:00.568
(Elsa screaming)
(soldier exclaiming)

448
00:38:02.196 --> 00:38:03.697
(panting)

449
00:38:03.864 --> 00:38:04.906
- I'm unhurt!

450
00:38:05.407 --> 00:38:06.741
- Get over here!

451
00:38:11.872 --> 00:38:13.999
- They're coming in from all sides.

452
00:38:27.805 --> 00:38:29.181
- Contact rear!

453
00:38:29.306 --> 00:38:30.765
(gunfire)

454
00:38:39.024 --> 00:38:40.025
- Go!

455
00:38:41.610 --> 00:38:42.944
Go!

456
00:38:48.242 --> 00:38:49.576
- Ah!

457
00:38:52.579 --> 00:38:54.706
- Elias. fall back.

458
00:38:59.002 --> 00:39:00.795
If you can hear me. fall back.

459
00:39:00.963 --> 00:39:01.922
- I'll hold them off

460
00:39:02.089 --> 00:39:03.131
and catch you up.

461
00:39:07.886 --> 00:39:09.762
(indistinct shouting)

462
00:39:14.351 --> 00:39:16.436
(beat-boxing)

463
00:39:34.371 --> 00:39:35.705
(brakes screeching)

464
00:39:40.836 --> 00:39:42.212
(Urdu): What's going on here?

465
00:39:47.301 --> 00:39:48.343
- Sir!

466
00:39:48.510 --> 00:39:52.722
Commandos came to rescue them!

467
00:39:53.432 --> 00:39:56.893
- They've relieved me
of the power to choose.

468
00:39:57.019 --> 00:39:59.396
So to start with...
(panting)

469
00:39:59.521 --> 00:40:02.273
...go get me that sniper's head
on a fucking plate now!!

470
00:40:02.399 --> 00:40:04.025
(all shouting)

471
00:40:05.110 --> 00:40:07.320
(shouting)

472
00:40:11.366 --> 00:40:13.242
(Elsa panting)

473
00:40:21.460 --> 00:40:23.211
- Sit down.

474
00:40:23.337 --> 00:40:25.047
(panting)

475
00:40:30.135 --> 00:40:31.302
(French): We lost 2 radio bags.

476
00:40:31.762 --> 00:40:33.305
- This one's dead.

477
00:40:34.389 --> 00:40:35.932
- The choppers'll be there.

478
00:40:38.477 --> 00:40:39.269
- Show me your arm.

479
00:40:39.603 --> 00:40:40.604
- Look after her.

480
00:40:40.771 --> 00:40:42.272
- Okay.

481
00:40:45.609 --> 00:40:47.444
- Rest assured. it'll be fine.

482
00:40:47.861 --> 00:40:49.445
You follow me.

483
00:40:49.613 --> 00:40:51.865
It's easier if you hold my pack.

484
00:40:53.200 --> 00:40:55.202
Come on. take my hand.

485
00:40:58.580 --> 00:40:59.622
Let's go.

486
00:41:07.172 --> 00:41:09.048
- Any tighter. I'll punch you.

487
00:41:10.676 --> 00:41:12.094
(groaning)

488
00:41:29.444 --> 00:41:31.195
(indistinct chatter)

489
00:41:37.327 --> 00:41:38.786
- Swarming with sharks.

490
00:41:38.954 --> 00:41:39.663
- GPS?

491
00:41:39.997 --> 00:41:41.999
- 36 north 72 east.

492
00:41:43.875 --> 00:41:45.710
- We can dodge them that way.

493
00:41:46.253 --> 00:41:48.255
- But we won't make the pick-up.

494
00:41:48.422 --> 00:41:49.714
- The distress signal?

495
00:41:49.881 --> 00:41:51.340
- The Taliban might locate it.

496
00:41:51.508 --> 00:41:52.842
- They already located us.

497
00:41:53.176 --> 00:41:54.510
- You and Marius go ahead.

498
00:41:54.636 --> 00:41:56.012
- Okay.
- Okay.

499
00:41:56.680 --> 00:41:59.140
- Where are we going?
- Later. We gotta move.

500
00:41:59.307 --> 00:42:00.224
- Can I help?

501
00:42:00.350 --> 00:42:03.728
- Sure. If you got a pack
of Howitzer and a radio.

502
00:42:04.271 --> 00:42:05.772
- Look who it is...

503
00:42:10.736 --> 00:42:12.362
- He's made some new friends.

504
00:42:34.217 --> 00:42:35.551
- It's the whole Mexican army!

505
00:42:35.719 --> 00:42:36.511
- C'mon. buddy.

506
00:42:38.722 --> 00:42:41.850
(panting)
(gunfire)

507
00:42:44.394 --> 00:42:46.437
- What's he doing?
- Winding them up.

508
00:42:53.445 --> 00:42:54.904
(panting)

509
00:42:58.617 --> 00:42:59.784
- They're playful.

510
00:43:01.661 --> 00:43:02.703
<i>- Wait...</i>

511
00:43:03.080 --> 00:43:03.955
Wait...

512
00:43:05.832 --> 00:43:06.457
Now!

513
00:43:07.000 --> 00:43:08.251
(shouting)

514
00:43:13.423 --> 00:43:14.632
(screaming)

515
00:43:17.594 --> 00:43:18.803
(sighing)

516
00:43:22.474 --> 00:43:24.225
- I don't know why.

517
00:43:24.726 --> 00:43:27.311
I hesitate more and more
about pushing a button.

518
00:43:28.313 --> 00:43:31.482
It's getting obsessive.
I'll mention it to my shrink.

519
00:43:31.733 --> 00:43:33.234
- Shut up and press. captain.

520
00:43:33.652 --> 00:43:34.527
- Yes. Marius.

521
00:43:34.694 --> 00:43:35.945
- Can I help?

522
00:43:41.910 --> 00:43:43.453
I'll change the dressing.

523
00:43:44.454 --> 00:43:45.580
- It needs closing up.

524
00:43:46.289 --> 00:43:47.081
- Sure.

525
00:43:47.249 --> 00:43:48.250
Of course.

526
00:43:48.583 --> 00:43:50.710
- We're 22 km from the pick-up.

527
00:43:50.877 --> 00:43:52.336
On top of the world's asshole.

528
00:43:52.504 --> 00:43:54.172
- There are ladies present.

529
00:43:54.464 --> 00:43:56.424
- Sorry. it must be the emotion.

530
00:43:59.094 --> 00:44:01.554
- By the way.
I'm not very good at sewing.

531
00:44:05.433 --> 00:44:06.475
Ready?

532
00:44:11.022 --> 00:44:11.772
Okay?

533
00:44:12.774 --> 00:44:13.483
- Fine.

534
00:44:18.738 --> 00:44:21.490
(beeping)

535
00:44:22.868 --> 00:44:24.119
- It's a distress signal.

536
00:44:24.286 --> 00:44:26.454
20 km from the pick-up.

537
00:44:27.205 --> 00:44:27.955
- Moving?

538
00:44:28.123 --> 00:44:28.665
- Negative.

539
00:44:32.544 --> 00:44:33.836
- We're 30 minutes ahead.

540
00:44:34.963 --> 00:44:37.882
- The choppers?
- They'll go to the pick-up first.

541
00:44:38.049 --> 00:44:38.966
- You okay?

542
00:44:39.134 --> 00:44:41.052
- We haven't eaten for 3 days.

543
00:44:41.219 --> 00:44:43.179
- Tell her to take her time.

544
00:44:45.640 --> 00:44:47.642
- Lucas took your article to heart.

545
00:44:47.851 --> 00:44:49.894
- The military doesn't like criticism.

546
00:44:52.981 --> 00:44:54.148
- They patch you up?

547
00:44:54.316 --> 00:44:55.025
- She did.

548
00:44:55.400 --> 00:44:57.443
- Really?
- Wipe that smile off.

549
00:44:57.611 --> 00:44:59.779
- Your analysis was interesting.
- Thanks.

550
00:45:00.906 --> 00:45:02.574
- I didn't say I agreed.

551
00:45:02.741 --> 00:45:05.493
Good or bad.
politics isn't our concern.

552
00:45:21.718 --> 00:45:23.720
(gunfire)

553
00:45:28.808 --> 00:45:31.060
(distant gunfire)

554
00:45:33.980 --> 00:45:35.231
- Lively down there.

555
00:45:35.398 --> 00:45:36.607
- What's going on?

556
00:45:36.983 --> 00:45:38.275
- Our taxis catching shit.

557
00:45:42.489 --> 00:45:44.282
- Gaining. 10 minutes behind.

558
00:45:44.866 --> 00:45:45.783
- Shit.

559
00:45:47.577 --> 00:45:48.661
Break time's over.

560
00:46:01.549 --> 00:46:02.925
- They failed.

561
00:46:03.927 --> 00:46:05.762
- Nobody at the pick-up zone.

562
00:46:05.929 --> 00:46:09.599
A chopper crash-landed.
with one man seriously wounded.

563
00:46:09.766 --> 00:46:10.975
- The hostages?

564
00:46:11.142 --> 00:46:13.769
- No news of the commandos
for 3 hours.

565
00:46:28.118 --> 00:46:32.122
(sniffling. panting)

566
00:46:32.247 --> 00:46:34.040
(soft music)

567
00:46:45.010 --> 00:46:46.678
(moaning softly)

568
00:47:15.081 --> 00:47:16.624
DAY 2

569
00:47:32.223 --> 00:47:34.516
Let's rest up.
she can't take any more.

570
00:47:37.145 --> 00:47:38.354
- Sit down.

571
00:47:48.656 --> 00:47:50.491
(Elsa groaning)

572
00:48:03.671 --> 00:48:05.255
- You have a Plan B?

573
00:48:05.673 --> 00:48:06.965
- No. there's no Plan B.

574
00:48:11.888 --> 00:48:13.347
- What's he plan on doing?

575
00:48:13.556 --> 00:48:14.765
- I don't know.

576
00:48:15.558 --> 00:48:17.601
Looking at him. we won't like it.

577
00:48:17.769 --> 00:48:19.103
- Here. captain.

578
00:48:20.647 --> 00:48:21.481
Victor.

579
00:48:24.192 --> 00:48:26.027
- Thank you.
- Mereci.

580
00:48:31.616 --> 00:48:33.117
- Well? What's the plan?

581
00:48:34.077 --> 00:48:36.704
- For Afghanistan.
we have one entry.

582
00:48:36.871 --> 00:48:37.955
And it's right there.

583
00:48:43.378 --> 00:48:44.754
- You're completely nuts.

584
00:48:46.589 --> 00:48:47.923
- What are they talking about?

585
00:48:48.174 --> 00:48:50.384
- We're here to get you back
and we will.

586
00:48:52.762 --> 00:48:54.346
Anybody got a better idea?

587
00:48:55.765 --> 00:48:56.974
Mm?

588
00:48:58.184 --> 00:49:01.520
- One hour of glory
beats an eternity of anonymity.

589
00:49:02.147 --> 00:49:03.898
(laughter)

590
00:49:19.372 --> 00:49:22.124
- Their chances get slimmer
by the hour.

591
00:49:22.292 --> 00:49:25.128
- Until proven otherwise.
we keep looking.

592
00:49:25.545 --> 00:49:27.296
I want everybody to stay alert.

593
00:49:45.899 --> 00:49:47.775
- How come you're here?

594
00:49:48.735 --> 00:49:49.944
- We parachuted in.

595
00:49:51.362 --> 00:49:52.529
- You know what I mean.

596
00:49:53.114 --> 00:49:54.406
- At last!

597
00:49:54.574 --> 00:49:57.743
I wondered
when the journalist would resurface.

598
00:49:58.828 --> 00:50:00.287
What do you want to know?

599
00:50:00.663 --> 00:50:03.540
How I wound up
with these boneheads in uniform?

600
00:50:03.833 --> 00:50:06.085
- No. I didn't mean that.

601
00:50:06.503 --> 00:50:08.838
- Sure.
We're not all Nobel prizewinners.

602
00:50:09.672 --> 00:50:10.964
But you guys neither.

603
00:50:12.050 --> 00:50:13.551
- Are you married?

604
00:50:14.344 --> 00:50:15.470
- Not right now.

605
00:50:19.599 --> 00:50:20.891
- Biscuits with your tea?

606
00:50:25.063 --> 00:50:26.773
- What?
- We'll never make it.

607
00:50:26.940 --> 00:50:28.608
- You'd rather sit and wait?

608
00:50:29.817 --> 00:50:31.610
- I hope you've called this right.

609
00:50:33.029 --> 00:50:34.238
- Me too.

610
00:50:34.781 --> 00:50:35.907
- You were very brave.

611
00:50:36.824 --> 00:50:37.908
- That's not bravery.

612
00:50:40.453 --> 00:50:42.663
Bravery
is that woman in the village.

613
00:50:43.581 --> 00:50:46.083
Before her execution.
she raised her burqa.

614
00:50:46.543 --> 00:50:47.961
Know what she did then?

615
00:50:49.420 --> 00:50:50.838
She smiled at them.

616
00:50:52.048 --> 00:50:53.549
And what did I do?

617
00:50:55.385 --> 00:50:56.636
Nothing at all.

618
00:51:00.515 --> 00:51:03.100
Sorry. I'm not much good
at chatting.

619
00:51:05.353 --> 00:51:06.479
You okay?

620
00:51:06.980 --> 00:51:07.772
- Sure.

621
00:51:15.071 --> 00:51:16.906
(background chatter)

622
00:51:22.078 --> 00:51:24.080
(gunfire)

623
00:51:37.135 --> 00:51:39.512
DAY 3

624
00:51:42.599 --> 00:51:43.308
- Tic Tac.

625
00:51:46.477 --> 00:51:47.728
-I'm on it

626
00:52:05.079 --> 00:52:06.288
- Is he trustworthy?

627
00:52:06.914 --> 00:52:07.664
- What?

628
00:52:07.832 --> 00:52:09.500
- Is he trustworthy. yes or no?

629
00:52:13.296 --> 00:52:16.048
- The Taliban massacred his family.
Good enough?

630
00:52:22.138 --> 00:52:23.931
- You can use this.

631
00:52:31.939 --> 00:52:33.357
Right.

632
00:52:33.858 --> 00:52:35.025
(Urdu): Thanks.

633
00:52:37.904 --> 00:52:39.906
(French): I believe breakfast is served.

634
00:52:53.544 --> 00:52:56.129
- They won't drop it.
- They like you too much.

635
00:53:01.844 --> 00:53:04.680
Elsa. why won't he let it go?

636
00:53:05.348 --> 00:53:07.099
- It became personal.

637
00:53:07.600 --> 00:53:09.351
- Sorry. I don't understand.

638
00:53:09.519 --> 00:53:11.145
- They're getting bigger here.

639
00:53:15.191 --> 00:53:18.194
- He can't lose face.
He'll do anything to get me.

640
00:53:18.361 --> 00:53:20.321
- It gets better and better.

641
00:53:22.407 --> 00:53:23.741
- Pay no attention.

642
00:53:26.119 --> 00:53:27.203
Go on.

643
00:53:34.043 --> 00:53:36.587
- Straight up.
3 days running from these jerks...

644
00:53:38.005 --> 00:53:40.007
- Yeah. aren't you sick of it?

645
00:53:49.058 --> 00:53:50.934
- You. stay with her.

646
00:53:51.060 --> 00:53:53.395
- Yes. sir.
(guns cocking)

647
00:54:05.867 --> 00:54:07.869
(men shouting)

648
00:54:33.895 --> 00:54:35.771
(shouting)

649
00:54:35.897 --> 00:54:37.315
- Contact front!

650
00:54:38.733 --> 00:54:41.235
- Go. go. go. go! Go! Go!

651
00:54:46.157 --> 00:54:47.867
(shouting)

652
00:55:06.385 --> 00:55:07.469
Go. go. go. go!

653
00:55:16.354 --> 00:55:18.356
- Go. go!

654
00:55:20.441 --> 00:55:21.442
(roaring)

655
00:55:21.567 --> 00:55:23.735
(distant gunfire)

656
00:55:56.394 --> 00:55:58.229
(indistinct shouting)

657
00:56:01.983 --> 00:56:03.985
(indistinct shouting)

658
00:56:10.533 --> 00:56:11.450
- I'm lead!

659
00:56:24.630 --> 00:56:26.840
(Elsa panting)

660
00:56:28.301 --> 00:56:30.594
(panting)

661
00:56:43.232 --> 00:56:44.983
(Urdu): Turn around! Go back!

662
00:56:45.985 --> 00:56:46.860
Turn around!

663
00:56:47.236 --> 00:56:48.403
- They're devils!

664
00:56:49.947 --> 00:56:51.281
- Go back up there!

665
00:56:51.449 --> 00:56:52.241
- Why?

666
00:56:52.408 --> 00:56:53.242
The Hindu Kush

667
00:56:53.409 --> 00:56:55.536
will vanquish the woman.

668
00:56:58.831 --> 00:57:00.374
(soft music)

669
00:57:00.833 --> 00:57:02.417
- Go back and kill her!

670
00:57:04.086 --> 00:57:04.753
Oakley!

671
00:57:08.090 --> 00:57:09.132
Western women

672
00:57:10.885 --> 00:57:12.970
are stronger than you think.

673
00:57:14.096 --> 00:57:15.305
Go on! Catch them!

674
00:57:18.267 --> 00:57:19.434
Go back!

675
00:57:44.627 --> 00:57:46.920
DAY 4

676
00:57:53.970 --> 00:57:55.346
(French): They're massacring us.

677
00:57:56.180 --> 00:57:58.098
"The reasons behind a fiasco.”

678
00:57:58.265 --> 00:58:00.141
"Defense indefensible."

679
00:58:02.895 --> 00:58:05.314
If we did nothing.
it'd be the same.

680
00:58:07.108 --> 00:58:10.694
Six guys are out there.
trying to bring her home.

681
00:58:28.129 --> 00:58:29.713
- Friend or enemy?

682
00:58:31.132 --> 00:58:32.800
- The next peak's 5.000 meters.

683
00:58:32.967 --> 00:58:35.511
We won't make it
without food and clothing.

684
00:58:40.099 --> 00:58:42.184
- What the hell are they doing?

685
00:58:45.354 --> 00:58:47.064
- What she is doing is very wise.

686
00:58:49.358 --> 00:58:50.817
She asks them for hospitality.

687
00:58:53.362 --> 00:58:56.365
We never refuse it.
Not even to an enemy.

688
00:59:00.536 --> 00:59:02.538
It's tradition.

689
00:59:15.885 --> 00:59:17.553
(Kovax): Next time. I tie you up.

690
00:59:18.804 --> 00:59:20.764
(indistinct chatter)

691
00:59:32.401 --> 00:59:34.945
- Ask him: Where are the children?

692
00:59:35.071 --> 00:59:36.572
(translating)

693
00:59:40.951 --> 00:59:42.994
- The Taliban came last summer

694
00:59:43.120 --> 00:59:46.331
and have taken away by force
all the children.

695
00:59:46.457 --> 00:59:48.417
Seventeen of them.
- What for?

696
00:59:48.626 --> 00:59:50.461
- Indoctrination in the madrassas.

697
00:59:51.337 --> 00:59:52.713
The children come home

698
00:59:53.089 --> 00:59:54.673
to impose sharia law.

699
00:59:54.924 --> 00:59:56.216
- Hmm.

700
00:59:56.884 --> 00:59:58.427
- No wonder they dislike them.

701
01:00:06.310 --> 01:00:08.645
- What do you think?
- Yeah. that one.

702
01:00:09.021 --> 01:00:09.980
It's a deal.

703
01:00:10.147 --> 01:00:11.606
- This one. too.

704
01:00:11.941 --> 01:00:14.318
- We'll take them all.
- They're great.

705
01:00:17.029 --> 01:00:18.613
(background chatter)

706
01:00:24.453 --> 01:00:25.912
(whistling)
- Bravo!

707
01:00:26.038 --> 01:00:28.165
- What?
(laughter)

708
01:00:28.290 --> 01:00:29.541
- Come and get it!

709
01:00:29.708 --> 01:00:31.000
Give me my hat!

710
01:00:31.168 --> 01:00:32.043
- Here. my friend.

711
01:00:32.211 --> 01:00:34.087
- What's a mushroom doing here?

712
01:00:36.090 --> 01:00:37.257
- Give me that!

713
01:00:37.424 --> 01:00:38.258
- Here...

714
01:00:41.011 --> 01:00:42.470
- I'll give it to you.

715
01:00:42.638 --> 01:00:43.513
- Fetch!

716
01:00:43.681 --> 01:00:44.640
- Here it is.

717
01:00:44.807 --> 01:00:46.809
- There you go. friend.
Suits you better.

718
01:00:47.059 --> 01:00:50.270
(gunshot)
- Oh! Hide! Hide! Hide! Hide!!

719
01:00:50.521 --> 01:00:51.730
(man): Get down!

720
01:00:51.897 --> 01:00:52.981
Hide!

721
01:00:53.482 --> 01:00:54.316
Take cover!

722
01:00:54.483 --> 01:00:55.567
- Get up!

723
01:00:56.527 --> 01:00:59.112
- He's dead! Victor. move it!

724
01:00:59.822 --> 01:01:01.448
Let go!

725
01:01:01.615 --> 01:01:02.782
He's dead!

726
01:01:03.868 --> 01:01:05.870
(screaming)

727
01:01:09.498 --> 01:01:11.291
(gunshot)

728
01:01:12.877 --> 01:01:14.670
(screaming)

729
01:01:15.087 --> 01:01:17.089
(shouting)

730
01:01:34.231 --> 01:01:36.858
(panting)

731
01:01:59.131 --> 01:02:01.550
(panting)

732
01:02:04.136 --> 01:02:06.721
(screaming)

733
01:02:26.283 --> 01:02:28.743
- Please. can you say a prayer for Marius?

734
01:02:30.162 --> 01:02:32.122
- It's an hon our.

735
01:03:15.541 --> 01:03:18.919
DAY 5

736
01:03:23.132 --> 01:03:25.217
(Elsa panting)
- Go. go. go. go!

737
01:03:45.446 --> 01:03:47.030
- Wait. Wait.

738
01:03:48.866 --> 01:03:50.033
Our path ends here.

739
01:03:50.826 --> 01:03:52.702
I have to stay.

740
01:03:55.456 --> 01:03:58.250
If I have to die in the mountains.
I prefer to die with them.

741
01:04:05.841 --> 01:04:07.551
(Urdu)

742
01:04:07.676 --> 01:04:10.095
(shouting orders)

743
01:04:10.220 --> 01:04:12.805
(shouting)

744
01:04:12.931 --> 01:04:14.307
- May God protect all of you.

745
01:04:18.228 --> 01:04:19.979
Thank you for saving my life.

746
01:04:20.189 --> 01:04:21.398
(French): I'm going with him.

747
01:04:21.732 --> 01:04:24.067
- Amin! Amin. wait. please.
Please. my friend.

748
01:04:24.401 --> 01:04:25.902
- We can't just let them go.

749
01:04:26.070 --> 01:04:27.905
- No martyrs! It's pointless.

750
01:04:28.072 --> 01:04:30.157
- Their hospitality's gonna
get them killed.

751
01:04:30.616 --> 01:04:31.408
- So what?

752
01:04:31.575 --> 01:04:34.286
We've already lost Marius
because of a dumb-ass journalist.

753
01:04:34.453 --> 01:04:36.329
We're not dying for some hicks.

754
01:04:38.415 --> 01:04:41.960
- The dumb-ass journalist
would rather stay with the hicks.

755
01:04:42.127 --> 01:04:43.503
- Negative!

756
01:04:44.380 --> 01:04:46.382
Lucas. stay with your new friend.

757
01:04:47.591 --> 01:04:49.092
We're going humanitarian.

758
01:05:05.734 --> 01:05:07.068
(bleating)

759
01:05:18.539 --> 01:05:20.541
- Asalaam aleikum.

760
01:05:21.166 --> 01:05:25.044
(Urdu): We're delighted
to have you in our village.

761
01:05:25.212 --> 01:05:28.924
Everybody wishes you a warm welcome.

762
01:05:31.343 --> 01:05:33.345
(people shouting and screaming)

763
01:05:38.517 --> 01:05:40.519
- Where is she?

764
01:05:40.686 --> 01:05:42.354
(shouting)

765
01:05:56.869 --> 01:05:57.995
Find her!

766
01:06:17.389 --> 01:06:19.099
(French): I'm sorry.

767
01:06:21.018 --> 01:06:22.561
I didn't mean what I said.

768
01:06:28.901 --> 01:06:31.361
(people screaming)
(automatic gunfire)

769
01:06:37.618 --> 01:06:39.411
(gunfire)

770
01:06:47.503 --> 01:06:48.712
(guns cocking)

771
01:07:03.101 --> 01:07:04.435
You never know.

772
01:07:12.778 --> 01:07:14.237
- Stop. stop. stop.

773
01:07:16.198 --> 01:07:18.074
- He loved this gun.

774
01:07:23.789 --> 01:07:24.623
For Marius.

775
01:07:27.876 --> 01:07:29.043
Go.

776
01:07:34.216 --> 01:07:36.051
(chatter)

777
01:07:45.894 --> 01:07:47.896
(heavy rock music)

778
01:08:16.091 --> 01:08:17.759
- Go!

779
01:08:17.884 --> 01:08:19.302
(panting)

780
01:08:24.516 --> 01:08:26.559
(grunting)

781
01:08:54.546 --> 01:08:57.340
Come on. go. Let's go. Hide.

782
01:09:12.773 --> 01:09:14.775
(distant gunfire)

783
01:09:16.360 --> 01:09:18.362
(panting)

784
01:09:19.363 --> 01:09:21.365
(shouting in French)

785
01:09:23.992 --> 01:09:25.326
(woman screaming)

786
01:09:25.452 --> 01:09:27.245
- Inside! Inside!
(gunfire)

787
01:09:27.371 --> 01:09:28.830
- Hey. come. Come on.

788
01:09:34.753 --> 01:09:35.962
(shouting)

789
01:09:39.341 --> 01:09:41.885
(French): I ever say I love this job?
- No. never.

790
01:09:42.052 --> 01:09:43.386
(shouting)

791
01:10:43.572 --> 01:10:45.282
- Go! Go! Go!

792
01:11:01.673 --> 01:11:03.675
(panting)
(distant gunfire)

793
01:11:11.475 --> 01:11:13.977
(shouting)

794
01:11:24.613 --> 01:11:26.031
- Shhh.

795
01:11:26.907 --> 01:11:29.117
Ah!

796
01:11:31.119 --> 01:11:33.121
(groaning)

797
01:11:47.761 --> 01:11:48.720
- Victor!

798
01:11:50.013 --> 01:11:50.888
Fuck!

799
01:11:52.682 --> 01:11:54.100
Victor's down! Fall back!

800
01:11:54.267 --> 01:11:55.768
Hold onto me!

801
01:11:56.728 --> 01:11:58.271
(groaning)

802
01:12:11.743 --> 01:12:13.369
(panting)

803
01:12:16.331 --> 01:12:18.416
(groaning)

804
01:12:18.542 --> 01:12:19.876
- Ah!!!

805
01:12:27.551 --> 01:12:28.718
(man): Magazine!

806
01:12:37.519 --> 01:12:38.520
Tic Tac!

807
01:12:41.189 --> 01:12:42.899
(roaring)

808
01:12:46.528 --> 01:12:47.362
- Amin's dead.

809
01:12:51.658 --> 01:12:52.492
- Magazine.

810
01:12:56.162 --> 01:12:57.705
- Go. I'll cover you.

811
01:12:58.790 --> 01:13:00.333
I'll be okay.

812
01:13:03.795 --> 01:13:04.420
Go on!

813
01:13:11.511 --> 01:13:12.970
(shouting in French)

814
01:13:13.471 --> 01:13:14.597
- Shit!

815
01:13:14.973 --> 01:13:16.057
- Take it easy!

816
01:13:16.224 --> 01:13:17.808
- Put him down there.

817
01:13:17.976 --> 01:13:21.771
(groaning)
(cursing in French)

818
01:13:21.897 --> 01:13:23.398
- Can you do a tourniquet?

819
01:13:23.565 --> 01:13:24.482
- It hurts!

820
01:13:24.691 --> 01:13:26.109
- Put your hands there.

821
01:13:26.276 --> 01:13:27.485
Press down hard.

822
01:13:27.652 --> 01:13:29.111
(Victor screaming)

823
01:13:29.613 --> 01:13:32.449
(screaming and cursing)
- Tic Tac!

824
01:13:34.367 --> 01:13:35.951
(groaning)

825
01:13:37.120 --> 01:13:37.829
- Amin?

826
01:13:41.374 --> 01:13:42.416
- Hang in there.

827
01:13:43.335 --> 01:13:44.377
Tough it out.

828
01:13:44.586 --> 01:13:46.421
- We wait for Elias?
- No.

829
01:13:48.006 --> 01:13:49.382
- Why not?

830
01:14:29.130 --> 01:14:30.840
(moaning)

831
01:14:34.928 --> 01:14:36.387
(man): Stop a minute!

832
01:14:37.806 --> 01:14:39.516
(groaning)

833
01:14:43.228 --> 01:14:44.229
- Leave me here.

834
01:14:46.022 --> 01:14:47.440
Leave me here.

835
01:14:47.607 --> 01:14:49.567
- Sure. when you stop breathing.

836
01:14:50.527 --> 01:14:52.320
Until then. hang in there.

837
01:14:52.612 --> 01:14:54.572
- Yes. boss.

838
01:14:56.408 --> 01:14:58.159
- We'll never make it.

839
01:14:59.369 --> 01:15:00.536
- What's the altitude?

840
01:15:01.871 --> 01:15:03.497
- 3.800. 3.900.

841
01:15:05.875 --> 01:15:07.334
It's starting to snow.

842
01:15:07.919 --> 01:15:09.378
The temperature's falling.

843
01:15:12.215 --> 01:15:13.049
- It ain't good.

844
01:15:13.216 --> 01:15:15.927
(Elsa reassuring him in French)

845
01:15:19.097 --> 01:15:20.389
- We need a shelter.

846
01:15:26.604 --> 01:15:27.980
- Victor. let's go.

847
01:15:28.314 --> 01:15:29.648
Elsa. take my blanket.

848
01:15:31.526 --> 01:15:34.237
(Victor screaming)
- C'mon. man! That's good.

849
01:15:37.949 --> 01:15:38.658
Good man!

850
01:15:45.540 --> 01:15:47.959
(soft music)

851
01:15:59.679 --> 01:16:02.139
DAY 6

852
01:16:04.184 --> 01:16:06.561
(wind blowing)

853
01:16:10.899 --> 01:16:13.735
(panting and groaning)

854
01:16:25.038 --> 01:16:26.456
- He's having convulsions.

855
01:16:26.748 --> 01:16:27.540
(man): Pin him down.

856
01:16:27.916 --> 01:16:28.791
Hold his legs.

857
01:16:28.958 --> 01:16:29.917
- I've got him.

858
01:16:32.504 --> 01:16:33.755
- More morphine?
- No way.

859
01:16:34.923 --> 01:16:35.965
It'd kill him.

860
01:16:38.676 --> 01:16:39.593
He's suffocating.

861
01:16:40.261 --> 01:16:41.887
Get his jaw open.

862
01:16:45.809 --> 01:16:47.227
(shouting in French)

863
01:16:48.770 --> 01:16:51.856
That's good. Victor. Come on!

864
01:16:53.817 --> 01:16:55.401
(speaking French)

865
01:16:59.739 --> 01:17:00.698
Deep breaths.

866
01:17:12.710 --> 01:17:14.169
(in French. to himself)

867
01:17:14.921 --> 01:17:17.214
- Deep breaths.

868
01:17:40.655 --> 01:17:41.989
Ah!

869
01:17:59.716 --> 01:18:01.759
(panting)

870
01:18:07.682 --> 01:18:09.392
(soft. dramatic music)

871
01:18:09.517 --> 01:18:11.519
(laboured breathing)

872
01:18:28.661 --> 01:18:31.205
You're as scared as me!

873
01:18:34.000 --> 01:18:35.835
I don't even hate you.

874
01:18:55.355 --> 01:18:57.357
(laboured breathing)

875
01:19:32.892 --> 01:19:34.059
- You okay?

876
01:19:35.478 --> 01:19:37.104
- I was far away. huh?

877
01:19:37.730 --> 01:19:39.690
- What matters is you're back.

878
01:19:41.734 --> 01:19:43.694
- Tic Tac lost his wife 9 years ago.

879
01:19:45.071 --> 01:19:47.114
I'd like him to be happy.

880
01:19:50.493 --> 01:19:51.577
- Rest.

881
01:21:12.241 --> 01:21:14.785
DAY 7

882
01:21:14.911 --> 01:21:18.748
- Ah! Victor!!
(grunting)

883
01:21:25.296 --> 01:21:27.881
(Elsa): Victor?!
(Kovax): Victor?!

884
01:21:29.342 --> 01:21:30.968
Victor?!!

885
01:21:33.846 --> 01:21:35.514
- Victor!

886
01:21:50.196 --> 01:21:52.406
- No!!

887
01:22:13.052 --> 01:22:14.094
- What are you doing?

888
01:22:17.640 --> 01:22:21.352
How many dead before you see
you'll never be back for them?

889
01:22:22.311 --> 01:22:23.520
Who's next. you or me?

890
01:22:27.859 --> 01:22:28.985
- What do you want?

891
01:22:29.152 --> 01:22:30.194
- Stop!

892
01:22:32.029 --> 01:22:32.904
Stop it!

893
01:22:35.825 --> 01:22:37.368
(repeating forcefully)

894
01:22:38.119 --> 01:22:39.787
You never listen!

895
01:22:40.413 --> 01:22:42.081
I'm staying here.

896
01:22:43.332 --> 01:22:45.083
- Do you have children?

897
01:22:45.585 --> 01:22:46.460
- No.

898
01:22:46.878 --> 01:22:49.755
- We're taking you home
and you can have loads.

899
01:22:53.176 --> 01:22:53.968
Listen up.

900
01:22:54.469 --> 01:22:56.095
Lisa is pregnant.

901
01:22:56.262 --> 01:22:59.640
Do me a favour.
make it home and take care of her.

902
01:23:47.730 --> 01:23:49.523
- I don't have kids either.

903
01:23:52.235 --> 01:23:54.403
- Is that an offer. captain?

904
01:23:55.696 --> 01:23:58.990
- I'm serious.
I'd really like to see you again.

905
01:24:08.251 --> 01:24:09.961
- I'm gonna be a dad?

906
01:24:13.756 --> 01:24:15.007
- Yes. buddy.

907
01:24:41.659 --> 01:24:45.788
DAY 8

908
01:24:55.089 --> 01:24:56.882
- Help me.

909
01:25:11.022 --> 01:25:13.149
- Why'd she suffer in silence?

910
01:25:14.150 --> 01:25:15.151
- Respect.

911
01:25:16.193 --> 01:25:17.611
- She's got guts.

912
01:25:18.029 --> 01:25:20.281
- Ballsy.
Wait for her to faint to be nice.

913
01:25:23.534 --> 01:25:25.536
(moaning)

914
01:25:30.833 --> 01:25:32.000
Don't look.

915
01:25:35.379 --> 01:25:36.588
It'll be okay.

916
01:25:51.854 --> 01:25:53.897
You know Victor's last words?

917
01:25:54.398 --> 01:25:55.941
- "I love this job."

918
01:26:10.706 --> 01:26:12.207
DAY 9

919
01:26:15.002 --> 01:26:18.213
- How do you become a reporter
in a war zone?

920
01:26:19.757 --> 01:26:21.467
- By falling in love

921
01:26:21.759 --> 01:26:23.677
with countries like this.

922
01:26:24.220 --> 01:26:26.639
- Choose Holland next time.

923
01:26:27.640 --> 01:26:28.682
- Why Holland?

924
01:26:28.849 --> 01:26:30.141
- It's flat.

925
01:26:33.145 --> 01:26:35.272
- Honestly.
how did you wind up here?

926
01:26:36.399 --> 01:26:38.067
- It was this or Holland.

927
01:26:38.693 --> 01:26:40.152
- Holland's cool.

928
01:26:40.319 --> 01:26:41.945
- Yeah. it's flat.

929
01:26:46.325 --> 01:26:46.992
- That's good.

930
01:26:47.159 --> 01:26:49.619
- Yeah. let's not talk about it.

931
01:26:50.246 --> 01:26:53.832
- Next time. I'll take you
to an Italian restaurant.

932
01:26:54.291 --> 01:26:56.626
Neapolitan specialties.
Near my place.

933
01:26:56.794 --> 01:26:57.920
You'll love it.

934
01:26:58.087 --> 01:27:00.631
They make wonderful risottos.

935
01:27:00.798 --> 01:27:03.175
Risotto with porcini mushrooms.

936
01:27:04.176 --> 01:27:06.970
- Maybe in another life.

937
01:27:08.389 --> 01:27:10.516
- It's not come to that yet.

938
01:27:10.683 --> 01:27:11.809
Don't worry.

939
01:27:12.059 --> 01:27:13.477
We'll make it.

940
01:28:37.770 --> 01:28:38.896
Contact!

941
01:28:39.063 --> 01:28:40.189
Take cover!

942
01:28:52.326 --> 01:28:54.369
(grunting)
(screaming)

943
01:29:05.631 --> 01:29:08.467
(panicked exclamations)

944
01:29:14.974 --> 01:29:16.684
- Ah!!

945
01:29:19.979 --> 01:29:21.981
(groaning)
- Lucas!

946
01:29:25.192 --> 01:29:26.818
(raging)

947
01:29:26.944 --> 01:29:27.611
Lucas!

948
01:29:40.791 --> 01:29:44.503
(panting frantically)
(screaming)

949
01:29:53.804 --> 01:29:55.806
(panicked exclamations)

950
01:30:14.074 --> 01:30:16.701
- Your fate is not yours to decide.

951
01:30:17.536 --> 01:30:18.828
(grunting)

952
01:30:19.872 --> 01:30:22.416
(screaming)

953
01:30:26.962 --> 01:30:28.338
(Kovax roaring)

954
01:30:46.440 --> 01:30:47.774
(Elsa screaming)

955
01:30:49.693 --> 01:30:51.069
- Lucas!

956
01:30:53.155 --> 01:30:55.198
Are you okay?

957
01:30:55.866 --> 01:30:57.450
(groaning in pain)

958
01:31:02.873 --> 01:31:04.040
Shit!

959
01:31:07.670 --> 01:31:08.962
You'll make it.

960
01:31:10.673 --> 01:31:11.799
It'll be okay.

961
01:31:15.427 --> 01:31:16.678
(sobbing)

962
01:31:16.845 --> 01:31:19.055
- It went too fast.

963
01:31:20.474 --> 01:31:22.309
(groaning)

964
01:31:30.150 --> 01:31:33.278
- No!!I No!!!

965
01:31:34.488 --> 01:31:36.490
No!!!

966
01:31:38.575 --> 01:31:39.659
You'll be okay!

967
01:31:42.121 --> 01:31:44.123
(sobbing)

968
01:31:52.506 --> 01:31:54.132
(panting)

969
01:31:57.136 --> 01:31:59.138
(soft music)

970
01:33:46.537 --> 01:33:48.747
DAY 10

971
01:34:03.679 --> 01:34:05.013
Okay!

972
01:34:05.139 --> 01:34:06.807
(groaning)

973
01:34:12.062 --> 01:34:13.480
(panting)

974
01:34:13.814 --> 01:34:15.941
- Shit. we've gone 3 km in 2 hours.

975
01:34:17.985 --> 01:34:20.028
- See the mountain we just crossed?

976
01:34:22.114 --> 01:34:23.824
That's the border.

977
01:34:26.410 --> 01:34:28.495
Welcome to Afghanistan.

978
01:34:44.136 --> 01:34:44.928
Move!

979
01:34:53.729 --> 01:34:56.106
(Tic Tac screaming)

980
01:35:05.073 --> 01:35:05.907
- Pull!

981
01:35:06.074 --> 01:35:07.658
(groaning)

982
01:35:07.784 --> 01:35:09.744
(grunting)

983
01:35:10.829 --> 01:35:12.163
(screaming)

984
01:35:26.094 --> 01:35:27.261
- I'll be okay.

985
01:35:49.952 --> 01:35:51.203
Elsa?

986
01:35:53.121 --> 01:35:54.705
Finish up without us.

987
01:36:07.594 --> 01:36:09.178
(gun cocking)

988
01:36:11.014 --> 01:36:12.181
Take it.

989
01:36:15.102 --> 01:36:17.104
- I'm not leaving you here.

990
01:36:17.479 --> 01:36:18.730
- Look at us.

991
01:36:21.233 --> 01:36:22.817
We can't go any farther.

992
01:36:25.862 --> 01:36:27.113
Please.

993
01:36:27.948 --> 01:36:29.199
Take it.

994
01:36:43.297 --> 01:36:44.965
- Take this compass. too.

995
01:36:48.677 --> 01:36:50.053
Take the compass.

996
01:36:52.014 --> 01:36:55.142
Keep heading west.

997
01:36:55.309 --> 01:36:57.519
West. Head west.

998
01:36:58.437 --> 01:37:00.272
- I can't leave you here.

999
01:37:01.440 --> 01:37:04.067
- You can and you're going to.

1000
01:37:04.526 --> 01:37:06.194
- I'm sorry. I can't.

1001
01:37:06.361 --> 01:37:09.113
- If not for yourself.
do it for the others.

1002
01:37:13.660 --> 01:37:16.496
- You have to make it
or it all means nothing.

1003
01:37:17.456 --> 01:37:18.748
- Go home.

1004
01:37:27.174 --> 01:37:28.133
- Go on.

1005
01:38:28.860 --> 01:38:29.861
- Go on.

1006
01:38:30.028 --> 01:38:31.112
Go.

1007
01:39:06.731 --> 01:39:08.482
She's hot for me.

1008
01:39:09.151 --> 01:39:10.360
- Sizzling.

1009
01:39:14.072 --> 01:39:15.239
- I love the girl.

1010
01:39:17.909 --> 01:39:19.285
She'll make it.

1011
01:39:41.975 --> 01:39:44.394
(thunder rumbling and crashing)

1012
01:39:58.200 --> 01:40:00.202
(panting)

1013
01:40:00.368 --> 01:40:01.827
- I'm going home.

1014
01:40:06.208 --> 01:40:08.210
(repeating)

1015
01:40:08.376 --> 01:40:10.002
Anyway. you're all dead!

1016
01:40:20.889 --> 01:40:23.892
DAY 11

1017
01:40:55.257 --> 01:40:57.259
(soft. haunting music)

1018
01:41:36.881 --> 01:41:39.258
DAY 12

1019
01:41:41.303 --> 01:41:42.721
- Admiral!
- Yes?

1020
01:41:44.764 --> 01:41:45.681
- She's alive.

1021
01:41:53.231 --> 01:41:56.108
- You'll be in Paris tomorrow.
- I won't leave Kabul.

1022
01:41:56.276 --> 01:41:57.860
- Your health is at stake.

1023
01:41:58.028 --> 01:42:00.071
- I'm staying till you get them.

1024
01:42:00.238 --> 01:42:03.241
- These people are here
to look after you.

1025
01:42:06.494 --> 01:42:07.912
- We have to go!
- Sorry.

1026
01:42:08.079 --> 01:42:09.246
Please...

1027
01:42:09.414 --> 01:42:10.832
Excuse me.

1028
01:42:20.175 --> 01:42:21.718
Climb up?
- Yes.

1029
01:42:21.885 --> 01:42:22.844
- What's going on?

1030
01:42:23.011 --> 01:42:25.179
- A quick flight and we'll be back.

1031
01:42:29.142 --> 01:42:30.226
- Admiral!

1032
01:42:30.393 --> 01:42:32.228
- Yes. I know. Minister.

1033
01:42:36.733 --> 01:42:37.817
- Thank you.

1034
01:42:38.485 --> 01:42:40.570
- For what? I should've found you.

1035
01:43:30.412 --> 01:43:33.039
(soft. haunting music)

1036
01:45:15.141 --> 01:45:18.018
For Jonathan and all French soldiers
fallen in Afghanistan.

1037
01:45:18.186 --> 01:45:21.272
And for all war reporters
who take risks

1038
01:45:21.439 --> 01:45:24.400
covering the news
all over the globe.

1039
01:45:30.323 --> 01:45:32.742
(soft. dramatic music)

1040
01:48:41.347 --> 01:48:43.682
Subtitling: CNST. Montreal
